  "texts": [
    "The PEs of the first slice then multiply 1/∥s∥ 2 2 by Ys * to obtain x, which is stored in a FF array that is accessible to all PE slices.Since the jth PE of the ith slice stores the jth row of Y i, it can compute line 4b by scaling si by x j.",
    "This is achieved in 12 clock cycles by circularly exchanging the entries of si across the 8 PEs of the ith PE slice, just as it is done for Cannon's algorithm (cf.",
    "Fig. 3(a)).",
    "The next step, given by line 5, is to use the PRNG module to generate u, which is used to start the power iteration that follows on lines 6a and 6b.",
    "The PRNG was implemented using xorshift [9] with a 64-bit state.The vector j of line 6b corresponds to an estimate of the jammer channel j, up to an unknown scale factor proportional to the jammer power."
  ],
